---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | Moonlight Peaks Wiki & Guide"
  description="How Moonlight Peaks Wiki & Guide handles cookies, analytics, and advertising."
  path="/privacy"
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Privacy' }]}
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="intro">How this site handles data, cookies, analytics, and advertising. Last updated {SITE.updated}.</p>

      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>Moonlight Peaks Wiki &amp; Guide ({SITE.url}) is an independent, fan-made guide site. You can reach us at {SITE.contact}.</p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        We use cookies and similar technologies for basic site function, to measure traffic, and —
        once enabled — to serve advertising. You can control or delete cookies through your browser
        settings. Where required by law, we ask for consent before non-essential cookies are set.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We may use a privacy-respecting analytics tool (such as Google Analytics) to understand
        which pages are useful. This collects aggregated data like page views, approximate region,
        and device type. It is not used to personally identify you.
      </p>

      <h2>Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        This site may display ads from third-party networks such as Google AdSense. These partners
        may use cookies to show relevant ads and measure performance. You can learn about and opt
        out of personalized advertising via Google's Ads Settings and the relevant industry opt-out
        pages for your region.
      </p>

      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live (for example, the EU/EEA, UK, or California), you may have rights
        to access, correct, or delete personal data, and to opt out of personalized ads. Contact us
        at {SITE.contact} to make a request.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy as the site grows or as advertising and analytics tools change. The "last updated" date above reflects the latest version.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
